t believe there’s an issue there. However, it might need some metadata for the test annotation in native contexts; I think that's where the agent collects information. So, I’ll take a closer look at the user-code-filter to understand it better and see if there's anything I need to adjust.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FhqXJYB7MAxUVxlhQE4G5Xny|fc_0506221318b8f7e20169fcc2375d1c81939802725bca916bde", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.camel/camel-support/4.19.0/user-code-filter.json"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 924, "output": 1512, "cacheRead": 10752, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 13188, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1778172447143, "responseId": "resp_0506221318b8f7e20169fcc21ff53881939a2a8c3d6880ba5d"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FhqXJYB7MAxUVxlhQE4G5Xny|fc_0506221318b8f7e20169fcc2375d1c81939802725bca916bde", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"rules\" : [\n    {\n      \"excludeClasses\" : \"**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\" : \"org.apache.camel.**\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"includeClasses\" : \"org_apache_camel.camel_support.**\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1778172472004}]}
